'''''Britain's Lost Masterpieces''''' is a factual [[BBC Four]] television series that aims to uncover overlooked [[art]] masterpieces in public collections, in conjunction with [[Art UK]].<ref name="Home">{{cite web|title=Britain's Lost Masterpieces - BBC Four|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b096mhvs|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=29 September 2017}}</ref><ref name="Jordaens">{{cite web|title=BBC Four’s Britain’s Lost Masterpieces discovers rare painting by 17th Century master Jacob Jordaens|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2016/britains-lost-masterpieces-jacob-jordaens|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=29 September 2017}}</ref> It is presented by [[Bendor Grosvenor]] and a companion. In series 1 this was [[Jacky Klein]]; in series 2, [[Emma Dabiri]]. Programmes also feature the [[art restoration|art restorer]], [[Simon Rollo Gillespie]].
