'''Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design''' is toy manufacturer located in [[Hochdorf, Esslingen|Hochdorf]], in Southern Germany.<ref>{{cite web|title=Grimm's company imprint|url=http://www.grimms.eu/index.php/en/imprint|publisher=Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design|accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref> Grimm's produces primarily wooden toys including puzzles, building blocks, baby rattles and stackers, doll houses and dollhouse furniture, stacking rainbows of many sizes, mobiles, decorative items, roll-along animals and vehicles, and more.  In 2013, Grimm's began producing their own line of [[Waldorf doll]]s. These dolls are a natural progression of their product line, which is inspired by [[Waldorf education]] (in Europe, commonly referred to as Steiner education). 

Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design (sometimes referred to as "Grimm's" or "Grimm's Spiel & Holz") was founded in 1978, at which time it was called Spiel und Holz Design. In 2006, the company came under new ownership, at which time the name was changed to Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design.<ref>{{cite web|title=Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design - ABOUT US|url=http://www.grimms.eu/index.php/en/about-us|publisher=Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design|accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref>

The wood used for Grimm's production is sourced from sustainably managed forests in Europe and includes alder, [[Tilia|lime]], [[Beech wood|beech]] and [[maple]]. The wood is cut into the forms then coated with natural oil. If the product is colored, the wood is then stain with certified non toxic, water-based colors.<ref>{{cite web|title=Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design - What we stand for|url=http://www.grimms.eu/index.php/en/what-we-stand-for|publisher=Grimm's Spiel und Holz Design|accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref>

Products from Grimm's are available in many countries worldwide, including the United States, often from independent and boutique toy stores, as well as several sources online, including Amazon.<ref>{{cite web|title=Grimm's toys on Amazon|url=https://www.amazon.com/s?ie=UTF8&field-brandtextbin=Grimm's&page=1&rh=n%3A165793011%2Cp_4%3AGrimm's|publisher=Amazon.com|accessdate=6 February 2013}}</ref>

